extends ../../../module_layout

block content

  .ui.container#raised-container
    .limit
      h1.ui.header.large#learn-title
        .content
          | Recognize the Techniques of Scammers
      h2 Example3:  Messages or Emails offer a coupon or gift card

      .imessage
        p.from-them
          | Congratulations! Youâ€™ve won a $1,000 Walmart gift card. Go to 
          u http://bit.ly/145634 
          | to claim now.

      p Here are signs that this message is a scam:
      ul
          li 
            | This message offers a coupon for a $1000 gift card. Is that too good to be true?
          li  
            | This message does not demonstrate an official source of Walmart.
          li 
            | This message invites you to click on a shortened foreign link. Legitimate links:
          ul
            li 
              | should be https://
            li 
              | should not shortened
            li 
              | should have no typos or misspelling
          li  
            | This message fails to provide fine prints, such as the expiration data or the exceptions to the sale. A legitimate coupon usually lists the details.
          
    .ui.icon.blue.message
        .icon
          img#dart_image1.ui.small.image.right.floated(src='/profile_pictures/transparent.png')
        .content
          .header
            //- i.info.circle.icon
            | Important!
          ul 
            li
              | If there's no fine print, the coupon is likely not legitimate.
            li 
              | No legitimate company will ask for personal information in exchange for a coupon. A popular scam is to offer coupons in exchange for completing surveys.
    
    script.
        var progress = #{user.moduleProgress.identity.percent}
    script(src='/js/setProgressBar.js')  

